        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 16 at 6:30PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 630 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 12 miles northwest of Two Buttes Reservoir, or 24 miles
northwest of Springfield, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Two Buttes Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
